Day_14 (Daily Problem)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Question:
-----------
Owofied a Sentence                                                                                  (02-08-2021)

Create a function that takes a sentence and turns every "i" into "wi" and "e" into "we", and add "owo" at the end.



Examples

owofied("I'm gonna ride 'til I can't no more")

? "I'm gonna rwidwe 'twil I can't no morwe owo"



owofied("Do you ever feel like a plastic bag")

? "Do you wevwer fwewel lwikwe a plastwic bag owo"



owofied("Cause baby you're a firework")

? "Causwe baby you'rwe a fwirwework owo"

Notes

Don't forget to return the value!

There's a space in front of owo!
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Solution:
-----------
#include<iostream>

using namespace std;



string owofied(string );

int main(){

	cout<<owofied("I'm gonna ride 'til I can't no more");

}

string owofied(string a){

	string temp="";

	for(int i=0;a[i]!='\0';i++){

		if(a[i]=='i'){

			temp=temp+"wi";

		}

		else if(a[i]=='e'){

			temp=temp+"we";

		}

		else{

			temp=temp+a[i];

		}

	}

	return temp+" owe";

}
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Learnings:
-------------
in this program we needed to enter a 2 digit word at a place of a single char. Replacing char (a[i])

with a 2 digit string is wrong

we created a temporary string "" and pasted the whole string in it using else condition

when we got i or e we added wi and we respectively to the new string .As nothing is in front in this case

so no need of shifting the chars in the original string . We simply made new string by copying each character 

and adding the new things on the making of new string

1.We learnt temporary string method of inserting other string in places of particular chars.

